@node MAIN "Start"


  If you are AmigaE user and want write your Esource with GOLDED, try
  these macros that  can help you in compilation of your programs.
  First of all read " Introduction "  please..but if curiosity is killing
  you, go to  @{" description " link Description}
 

  @{" Introduction " link Introduction}
  @{" What are these ? " link Description}
  @{" Restrictions " link Restrictions}
  @{" Thank's " link Thank}
  @{" Author " link Author}
@endnode

@node Introduction "introduction"

  I am a registered user of E compiler ( Thank's Wouters !) and I write my
  programs with EE the editor included in AmigaE distribuition.
  For curiosity in these days I have tried to use Golded. It's a Great EDitor
  but its initial configuration is not useful for E user ( it's ONLY a my
  opinion...), so I have given a look on Arexx directory and Aminet.
  I have found these programs:

  - Economic ( dev/e ) the perfect interface to EC from a editor
  - E parser from  ged_e-s2.lha  ( text/edit )
  - E scanner from escanner.lha  ( text/edit ? )

 I have added some macros so with this mixage GED seems more friendly for E user

  Conclusion: at end of my short excursion in GoldED world, I came back to EE.
  I didn't become a registered user of GoldED because my affection for EE ( it
  has all I need for my simple E programs ).
  My impression about GoldED was ( and IS ) that it's a Great EDitor ( infact
  I have tried to write some macros for it.. )
  As said my very old forefather " veni, vidi, written " :-)

  NB: a simple advice about GoldED by @{" MaP " link Author}  : TRY IT !

@endnode

@node Description "Well-come"

  Macros or arexx programs to run from GoldED ( macros menu )
  These macros make work for you and it's a good work!

  Some of them are "new" others are adapted from existent one.
  Go to the description and read the scripts.

  @{" Eversion.ged " link Eversion}
  @{" Ecomment.ged " link Ecomment}
  @{" UnEcomment.ged " link UnEcomment}
  @{" UnEcomment_mini.ged " link UnEcomment_mini}
  @{" Efold.ged " link Efold}
  @{" DelEfold.ged " link DelEfold}



  If you have some doubt please read the scripts or.. @{" EMail " link Author} me
@endnode

@node EVERSION "Eversion.ged"

  ** Eversion.ged **

  Add a string version in a Esource

  I use this form at last of my Esource :
    VOID: '$VER NameProg  x.x (DATE) by MaP'
                          ^ ^
                   version  revision

  - no control on existent string version
  - control on file that must be < file.e >
    ( if not a requester will remeber it )
  - Version.Revision printed 0.1
  - format date printed DD.MM.YY
  - after execution cursor will be on Version number

@endnode

@node ECOMMENT "Ecomment.ged"

 Note: comment in E begin "/*" end "*/"  (for a single line there is "->" too)

 ** Ecomment.ged **

 change a selected  block in a commented block ( so the block is hiding
 for E compiler )

 - block must be selected
   ( if not a requester will remember it )
 - first E comment marker printed "/* -- EComment --" ( begin of block )
 - last E comment marker printed  "-- EComment -- */" ( after block )
 - after execution block mark removed

@endnode

@node UNECOMMENT "UnEcomment.ged"

  ** UnEcomment.ged **

  Remove a commented block

  - delete E comment markers added by Ecomment
  - control on *TWO* E comment markers
    (requester if these markers are not found)

  It works ONLY on one block

@endnode

@node UNECOMMENT_MINI "UnEcomment_mini.ged"


  ** UnEcomment_mini.ged **

  Like UnEcomment but there is NOT control on presence of second
  E comment marker.

  My think was: if I have used Ecomment.ged must be present *TWO*
  E comment markers. Why have I to control the presence of the second ?

  Answer A : UnEcomment_mini
  Answer B : why not ? ( see UnEcomment..)

@endnode

@node EFOLD "EFold.ged"


  ** Efold.ged **

  Fold  a block ( for Esources )

  Using GED fold markers ( /// ), fold block is NOT hiding for EC (give error)
  I have read fold.ged 1.0, ©1996 Dietmar Eilert and made some modification.
  I have added Ecomment marker ( "/*  */") before and after GED fold markers
  and a control of marked block. Efold.ged is more "professional" than
  Ecomment.ged  but has same effect for E sources.
  

  Efold markers printed "/* ///"  "/// */"
@endnode
@node DELEFOLD "DelEFold.ged"


  ** DelEfold.ged **

  Remove fold markers ( the line where they are )

  You must unfold the fold , then run DelEfold .This macro delete FIRST TWO
  markers of Esource. I have used the presence of default fold markers ( /// )

@endnode

@node Restrictions "Restrictions"


 WHAT ?? Restrictions on these miserable macros ?? Come on, be serious...

 I am not a registered user of GED, macros are only a little help for
 AmigaE users ( I hope...) and I have "used" others macros so...
 you can do everything of these macros but REMEBER:

              NOBODY has property but EVERYBODY has use !!

@endnode
